1
00:00:55,556 --> 00:00:58,142
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

2
00:00:58,225 --> 00:01:00,227
[tense music plays]

3
00:01:01,103 --> 00:01:02,271
[Woo-seok] <i>Syria?</i>

4
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:04,231
[tires squealing]

5
00:01:04,315 --> 00:01:05,608
[exclaiming]

6
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,239
[pants]

7
00:01:14,909 --> 00:01:15,910
[exhales sharply]

8
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:20,247
[pants]

9
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:22,792
[groans]

10
00:01:26,462 --> 00:01:27,463
[groans]

11
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:31,926
[groans]

12
00:01:33,177 --> 00:01:35,429
[groans]

13
00:01:35,513 --> 00:01:36,972
[winces]

14
00:01:37,932 --> 00:01:38,933
[groans]

15
00:01:40,893 --> 00:01:41,977
[sighs]

16
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:47,691
[mysterious music plays]

17
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:58,661
[pants]

18
00:02:01,372 --> 00:02:02,498
[pants]

19
00:02:08,379 --> 00:02:10,631
{\an8}EPISODE 7

20
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,720
{\an8}Han Seol-ah was the first to call it in.

21
00:02:18,097 --> 00:02:19,765
{\an8}She even gave a witness statement.

22
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,270
{\an8}I'll call you back, all right?

23
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,022
{\an8}[line disconnects]

24
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:28,899
{\an8}[Gong sighs]

25
00:02:29,859 --> 00:02:33,404
{\an8}You happened to be at the scene
at that exact moment?

26
00:02:35,614 --> 00:02:37,199
Another coincidence?

27
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:42,079
{\an8}Here's the dashcam footage from my call.

28
00:02:43,706 --> 00:02:45,374
{\an8}Got an alibi this time too.

29
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,251
{\an8}There seems to be a misunderstanding.

30
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:50,921
{\an8}I'm just offering this
in case it helps with the investigation.

31
00:02:53,132 --> 00:02:54,633
[Gong] So, you're confident?

32
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:56,844
We'll find out with the forensics.

33
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:09,982
MISSED CALL
SEOL-AH

34
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:22,119
Captain, you need to see this.

35
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:25,623
APPROVED TRANSACTIONS
DOMESTIC & INTERNATIONAL

36
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:28,626
Do Eun-hye submitted this. They were
together at the time of the accident.

37
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:31,170
Their parents' house and his studio
are both in Cheongun,

38
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:32,671
so they were there every weekend.

39
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:35,674
LIST OF EVIDENCE: RECEIPT
DAEYONGRU CHEONGUN BRANCH: AUGUST 17, 2025

40
00:03:38,177 --> 00:03:39,803
- Since Woo-seok's accident…
- [sighs]

41
00:03:39,887 --> 00:03:41,931
…happened while he was here too,

42
00:03:43,015 --> 00:03:45,309
could it be that we got it all wrong?

43
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,733
[sighs]

44
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,905
[tense music plays]

45
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:04,161
What if there's another accomplice?

46
00:04:05,371 --> 00:04:06,497
What about Do Eun-hyuk?

47
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:09,249
It's possible Han Seol-ah
has been dragging him

48
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:10,709
to every crime scene for an alibi.

49
00:04:11,794 --> 00:04:12,878
[gasps]

50
00:04:14,213 --> 00:04:16,340
So, the real player is somewhere else?

51
00:04:27,059 --> 00:04:29,019
[huffs] Are you an idiot or something?

52
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:31,397
Why would you fix
someone else's yacht, huh?

53
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,899
- You just do as you're told.
- [line rings]

54
00:04:33,983 --> 00:04:36,193
What would have happened
if it weren't for me?

55
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:39,196
[scoffs] Seriously?

56
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,364
Hey!

57
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:43,242
[knocks]

58
00:04:49,206 --> 00:04:51,208
[dramatic music plays]

59
00:05:04,847 --> 00:05:08,225
[Kwang-jin] <i>Jun-beom, he started</i>
<i>volunteering with OnWorld back in college.</i>

60
00:05:09,143 --> 00:05:11,103
Even though his family
was pretty well-off.

61
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:13,772
He was interested
in helping people in need.

62
00:05:13,856 --> 00:05:15,899
Did he do volunteer work?

63
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:18,861
[scoffs] If only
that hadn't happened in Syria.

64
00:05:19,528 --> 00:05:20,529
[Woo-seok] <i>Syria?</i>

65
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:23,615
[sighs]

66
00:05:34,084 --> 00:05:36,420
You could've ended up just like that.

67
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:38,464
I'm telling you

68
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:40,799
you could've just died.

69
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:43,469
And you still trust Han Seol-ah?

70
00:05:44,178 --> 00:05:45,179
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

71
00:05:45,262 --> 00:05:47,681
What? You think that woman saved you
or something?

72
00:05:47,765 --> 00:05:50,267
- [sighs]
- It's just like with Kim Yun-ji case.

73
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,937
Han Seol-ah was at every scene
but her alibi is solid.

74
00:05:55,481 --> 00:05:56,607
So what?

75
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:58,317
Just a coincidence?

76
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,194
Shouldn't we assume there's an accomplice?

77
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:06,533
[sighs]

78
00:06:07,493 --> 00:06:09,286
It wasn't Do Eun-hyuk.

79
00:06:09,912 --> 00:06:12,414
He was at the police station
being questioned.

80
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:14,208
Well…

81
00:06:15,459 --> 00:06:18,170
she's the type who could control
anyone she wanted to.

82
00:06:19,922 --> 00:06:22,382
And there might be another person
involved as well.

83
00:06:27,513 --> 00:06:30,224
But what would she gain
by getting rid of me or Lee Kwang-jin?

84
00:06:30,808 --> 00:06:31,809
Huh?

85
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:35,562
Are you so convinced it's Han Seol-ah
that you're blinded by it?

86
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,232
What if the real culprit is someone else?

87
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:41,527
[sighs] So, you're saying someone targeted
only the people around Han Seol-ah?

88
00:06:45,781 --> 00:06:48,617
You have something else, don't you?

89
00:06:52,538 --> 00:06:54,123
[sighs]

90
00:06:54,206 --> 00:06:58,210
The accident happened
while tracking a suspect.

91
00:06:58,293 --> 00:06:59,461
Who's that?

92
00:07:00,504 --> 00:07:01,547
Paek Jun-beom.

93
00:07:02,965 --> 00:07:04,133
But why him?

94
00:07:04,216 --> 00:07:07,094
He sold the wine exclusively
at Yoon Seung-jae's restaurant,

95
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:09,763
and was at the scene
the day Kim Yun-ji died.

96
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:16,520
That's not all.
Paek Jun-beom was in Syria as well.

97
00:07:17,271 --> 00:07:18,772
Syria?

98
00:07:18,856 --> 00:07:20,190
That's where Lee Su-ho died.

99
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:23,318
Are you saying there's a connection
between those two?

100
00:07:24,194 --> 00:07:25,988
Lee Su-ho worked for OnWorld,

101
00:07:27,114 --> 00:07:29,074
and Paek Jun-beom was a volunteer there.

102
00:07:30,534 --> 00:07:32,953
Paek Jun-beom is the one
tied to all the deaths…

103
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,081
{\an8}surrounding Han Seol-ah.

104
00:07:40,544 --> 00:07:43,755
PAEK JUN-BEOM (35 YEARS OLD)
CEO OF YOUR HOME

105
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:47,092
Someone with money, time,
and the ability to pull it off.

106
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:51,054
Someone who crossed paths with Kim Yun-ji.

107
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,731
HWANG SUK-JI (37 YEARS OLD)
CAFE THIRD NIGHT, HAN SEOL-AH'S FRIEND

108
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,691
Maybe an uninvited guest

109
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:05,194
who snuck into the auction house
that night.

110
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:12,910
Whose trail should we check first?

111
00:08:24,213 --> 00:08:26,590
[door opens]

112
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,179
Isn't it too soon for you
to be moving around?

113
00:08:34,348 --> 00:08:35,515
I'm okay.

114
00:08:37,059 --> 00:08:38,227
[sighs]

115
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:41,104
I'm more worried
about Mr. Lee Kwang-jin though.

116
00:08:45,943 --> 00:08:47,778
What brought you
to the scene of the accident?

117
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:56,495
Is there anything you remember? Anything?

118
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,630
I got the hint from that painting.

119
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:10,926
[melancholy music plays]

120
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:12,886
[sighs]

121
00:09:17,391 --> 00:09:18,392
Syria…

122
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:29,653
I passed your message on to Mr. Lee,
but don't wait for a response.

123
00:09:30,487 --> 00:09:33,907
He wanted to tell you
he has nothing further to say, Ms. Han.

124
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:35,909
I'm so sorry.

125
00:09:37,661 --> 00:09:39,371
When will he be back
from his trip to Laos?

126
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:40,580
Oh…

127
00:09:40,664 --> 00:09:41,665
Actually,

128
00:09:42,249 --> 00:09:43,875
he's flying back from Laos tonight.

129
00:09:50,007 --> 00:09:53,176
[Seol-ah] <i>I was on my way to meet</i>
<i>Mr. Lee Kwang-jin at the airport,</i>

130
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:54,344
<i>when I saw your car.</i>

131
00:09:56,513 --> 00:09:58,515
[ominous music plays]

132
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:03,186
<i>Behind you, I saw the same black car</i>
<i>that had been following us</i>

133
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,646
<i>right on your tail.</i>

134
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:15,365
[exclaims]

135
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:26,585
<i>I had a bad feeling,</i>
<i>so I immediately turned the car around.</i>

136
00:10:56,323 --> 00:10:57,324
Woo-seok!

137
00:10:58,075 --> 00:10:59,076
Woo-seok!

138
00:11:11,588 --> 00:11:12,589
[sighs]

139
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:14,383
[sympathetic music plays]

140
00:11:14,466 --> 00:11:16,176
You saved me, Seol-ah.

141
00:11:17,386 --> 00:11:19,471
Anyone passing by would've done the same.

142
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:25,894
But…

143
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:29,815
what was the culprit trying to do?

144
00:11:30,857 --> 00:11:32,901
He was trying to silence Mr. Lee.

145
00:11:34,569 --> 00:11:35,570
Paek Jun-beom

146
00:11:36,863 --> 00:11:39,324
had been an OnWorld volunteer
since college.

147
00:11:39,908 --> 00:11:42,119
He was in Syria with Lee Su-ho as well.

148
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:44,996
<i>An Orphan from Syria</i>.

149
00:11:46,289 --> 00:11:47,958
He sent that painting on purpose too.

150
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,836
[sighs] Probably.

151
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,421
Why?

152
00:11:53,296 --> 00:11:57,467
Just because he worked with Su-ho. Is that
really enough reason to go this far?

153
00:11:57,551 --> 00:11:59,136
Mr. Lee may be the only one

154
00:12:00,262 --> 00:12:03,306
who knew why Paek Jun-beom approached us.

155
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,724
[sighs]

156
00:12:04,808 --> 00:12:06,560
He will be the only one who knows,

157
00:12:08,103 --> 00:12:10,021
unless Mr. Lee wakes up.

158
00:12:15,861 --> 00:12:18,864
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

159
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:19,948
[phone buzzes]

160
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:23,410
SENIOR MANAGER CHA

161
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:25,412
[Woo-seok] <i>Mr. Ahn, stake out</i>
<i>the hospital until Mr. Lee wakes up.</i>

162
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:26,496
<i>Keep it discreet.</i>

163
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:30,834
[inquisitive music plays]

164
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:39,217
[chuckles]

165
00:12:39,301 --> 00:12:40,719
My first mission as an SIU member.

166
00:12:40,802 --> 00:12:42,679
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE SIU
ASSISTANT MANAGER AHN YOUNG-SOO

167
00:12:43,472 --> 00:12:44,973
I'll make sure to see it through.

168
00:12:45,807 --> 00:12:46,975
[gasps, moans]

169
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:51,104
[clears throat]

170
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:53,857
VIOLENT CRIMES UNIT 1

171
00:12:56,485 --> 00:12:58,403
The dashcam results are finally in.

172
00:13:05,869 --> 00:13:07,662
- [taps keyboard]
- Take a look at this.

173
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:11,124
[intense music plays]

174
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,710
That's who caused the accident.

175
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:17,005
It may take some time
to identify the license plate

176
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:20,217
- but we've confirmed the make and model.
- Was the accident recorded?

177
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,468
[taps keyboard]

178
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:22,677
Right here.

179
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:34,231
[both sigh]

180
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:40,820
[sighs]

181
00:13:40,904 --> 00:13:42,280
She went to save him.

182
00:13:42,864 --> 00:13:44,741
I think she really is just a witness.

183
00:13:48,495 --> 00:13:50,705
PORTRAITS OF A WOMAN: SPECIAL EXHIBITION

184
00:13:50,789 --> 00:13:52,832
[footsteps approaching]

185
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,209
[Seol-ah] For this auction,

186
00:13:54,292 --> 00:13:57,295
I'm placing the artist who had that
intense bidding war towards the beginning.

187
00:13:57,379 --> 00:14:00,507
And I've scheduled the Stiller
as the 30th lot--

188
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:03,385
With this lineup, it's going to be intense
right from the start.

189
00:14:04,052 --> 00:14:06,721
You're really determined to hit a record
price, aren't you?

190
00:14:06,805 --> 00:14:09,599
- [chuckles]
- [client speaking in Spanish]

191
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:13,311
[continues speaking Spanish]

192
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:16,147
[Na-hee, in English] Oh, uh, Spanish, huh?

193
00:14:16,231 --> 00:14:17,649
Just a moment, please.

194
00:14:17,732 --> 00:14:18,817
[in Spanish] Sir?

195
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,947
- Can I help you?
- Do you speak Spanish?

196
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,448
Yes, just a little.

197
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:26,741
[client] Thank goodness.

198
00:14:27,242 --> 00:14:28,368
I like this painting.

199
00:14:29,244 --> 00:14:30,912
Is it possible to negotiate the price?

200
00:14:31,621 --> 00:14:34,499
You're a valued guest
who has traveled a long way,

201
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:40,213
so of course, we can do that for you.

202
00:14:40,297 --> 00:14:41,298
Thank you.

203
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:42,799
Thank you very much.

204
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:45,844
[in English] He's going ahead
with the payment. Get everything ready.

205
00:14:45,927 --> 00:14:46,970
Of course, ma'am.

206
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,682
- [Chair Kim, in Spanish] Thank you.
- [client] Thank you.

207
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:58,523
[in English] So,
did you study art in Spain, ma'am?

208
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:02,110
When I was pushed out of the company
for selling a forgery,

209
00:15:03,695 --> 00:15:06,072
not a single person
reached out to help me.

210
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,908
So I packed my bags and flew out.

211
00:15:09,618 --> 00:15:11,036
I scrubbed floors at first

212
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:16,041
and I learned that if I wanted to survive,
then I had to learn the language first.

213
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,586
I picked it up by ear
and copied what I heard.

214
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:23,757
And thanks to that,
I managed to secure a few art pieces.

215
00:15:24,341 --> 00:15:27,719
That became my leverage
to return to Royal Auction,

216
00:15:27,802 --> 00:15:29,095
and that's how I survived.

217
00:15:29,846 --> 00:15:31,598
So, I packed my bags and left.

218
00:15:32,807 --> 00:15:34,476
You're truly remarkable, ma'am.

219
00:15:35,977 --> 00:15:39,147
To be able to rise again
after losing everything like that.

220
00:15:39,648 --> 00:15:42,942
Most people would just give up
after losing all they had.

221
00:15:43,902 --> 00:15:45,737
That's usually how it goes, ma'am.

222
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:49,115
If you've lost everything,

223
00:15:49,824 --> 00:15:51,993
you have nothing left to lose

224
00:15:52,911 --> 00:15:55,246
- and nothing left to fear.
- [elevator dings]

225
00:15:55,330 --> 00:15:56,873
[elevator doors open]

226
00:16:06,508 --> 00:16:09,511
[tense music plays]

227
00:16:12,597 --> 00:16:14,516
TAEMYUNG GROUP

228
00:16:14,599 --> 00:16:16,101
[mouse clicks]

229
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:20,230
FIRE BREAKS OUT ON A TRUCK TRANSPORTING
TAEMYUNG CULTURAL FOUNDATION ART

230
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:22,941
DAMAGE WORTH TENS OF BILLIONS OF WON,
NO CASUALTIES REPORTED

231
00:16:26,069 --> 00:16:29,072
[Seol-ah] 1.5 million, any takers?

232
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:36,371
- [crowd gasping]
- <i>Vanished Sensation</i> by Fabien Leclerc

233
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:39,290
is sold to Chairman Park Min-cheol
of Taemyung Group.

234
00:16:39,874 --> 00:16:41,459
Please make sure
to give this to Chair Kim.

235
00:16:41,543 --> 00:16:44,462
This exhibition was only possible
thanks to her.

236
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:47,424
The five pieces he won
at the last special auction

237
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:50,009
will be exhibited
at the Busan Taemyung Art Center.

238
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,345
Busan?

239
00:16:56,933 --> 00:17:00,145
[dramatic music plays]

240
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:10,822
PLEASE ENTER YOUR PASSWORD
TO UNLOCK THIS DRIVE

241
00:17:12,991 --> 00:17:15,827
TAEMYUNG GROUP AUCTION ARTWORK LIST

242
00:17:17,787 --> 00:17:19,038
VANISHED SENSATION,
THE REMAINS OF ECSTASY

243
00:17:19,122 --> 00:17:20,123
THE ABYSS, ECHO, TURBULENCE

244
00:17:24,711 --> 00:17:29,466
GANGHA POLICE STATION

245
00:17:30,175 --> 00:17:34,637
The suspect's vehicle is a black sedan,
plate ending in 4549.

246
00:17:34,721 --> 00:17:36,681
A ghost car fitted
with a canceled license plate.

247
00:17:39,309 --> 00:17:42,270
It came out onto Yeongjong Bridge
and headed toward Gangseo-gu.

248
00:17:42,353 --> 00:17:43,980
4549 MOVEMENT ROUTE

249
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:46,441
When was the car last seen?

250
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:47,734
[Gong] Here.

251
00:17:52,489 --> 00:17:54,866
[dramatic music plays]

252
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:08,588
I've seen him before.

253
00:18:13,176 --> 00:18:14,177
[elevator dings]

254
00:18:23,269 --> 00:18:25,313
[worker] Flower delivery
for Ms. Han Seol-ah.

255
00:18:25,855 --> 00:18:28,066
- Oh, right there. That's her office.
- Oh. Thank you.

256
00:18:30,151 --> 00:18:31,611
Flower delivery.

257
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,366
Who is it from?

258
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:38,409
One moment please. [sighs]

259
00:18:38,493 --> 00:18:40,453
It was sent anonymously.

260
00:18:40,537 --> 00:18:41,538
Have a good one.

261
00:18:53,758 --> 00:18:55,218
[Su-ho] Happy birthday.

262
00:19:09,524 --> 00:19:12,068
[contemplative music plays]

263
00:19:33,548 --> 00:19:35,216
[dramatic music plays]

264
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:52,942
[sighs] My gosh.

265
00:19:53,026 --> 00:19:55,320
I though Mr. Cha was just good-looking,

266
00:19:55,403 --> 00:19:57,572
but it turns out
he's a total romantic too.

267
00:19:57,655 --> 00:20:00,658
Ms. Han even gets a confession like that.
I'm jealous.

268
00:20:01,242 --> 00:20:02,660
Confession?

269
00:20:02,744 --> 00:20:06,664
You didn't you know? The meaning
of lisianthus flowers is eternal love.

270
00:20:06,748 --> 00:20:07,749
[Na-hee exclaims]

271
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:12,003
So, that means
you like flowers too, ma'am?

272
00:20:12,587 --> 00:20:15,298
[scoffs] What woman doesn't like flowers,
hmm?

273
00:20:25,892 --> 00:20:27,894
[mournful music plays]

274
00:20:44,494 --> 00:20:45,703
[sighs softly]

275
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:06,766
<i>S-Seol-ah.</i>

276
00:21:09,018 --> 00:21:10,061
<i>If I disappear…</i>

277
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:14,148
<i>you'd be happy, wouldn't you?</i>

278
00:21:18,069 --> 00:21:19,404
<i>That's…</i>

279
00:21:21,948 --> 00:21:23,241
<i>It's what you want, isn't it?</i>

280
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:28,121
<i>I no longer have a reason to live.</i>

281
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:32,166
<i>Even if I had to die to stay with you…</i>

282
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:35,878
<i>I would do it.</i>

283
00:21:37,422 --> 00:21:39,382
[Su-ho laughs]

284
00:21:40,425 --> 00:21:42,719
<i>I know. I know I'm crazy.</i> [sniffles]

285
00:21:43,594 --> 00:21:47,849
<i>But if it means</i>
<i>you'll remember me forever…</i>

286
00:21:51,102 --> 00:21:52,520
<i>I'll be the bad guy.</i>

287
00:21:59,152 --> 00:22:00,236
[Seol-ah] You and I…

288
00:22:01,863 --> 00:22:03,281
want different things.

289
00:22:05,742 --> 00:22:08,703
I just barely got the internship
at the auction house.

290
00:22:08,786 --> 00:22:11,164
And this opportunity
means everything to me.

291
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:14,333
So, are you saying
I'm not worth fitting into your life?

292
00:22:14,417 --> 00:22:15,626
Su-ho…

293
00:22:19,464 --> 00:22:22,383
Who are you with right now?
Why didn't you answer?

294
00:22:22,467 --> 00:22:23,801
I'm working.

295
00:22:23,885 --> 00:22:27,346
Hey. Aren't you with that
photographer bastard now?

296
00:22:27,430 --> 00:22:28,639
Just stop it please.

297
00:22:28,723 --> 00:22:30,266
So it's all over now, huh?

298
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:32,018
That's like telling me to die.

299
00:22:32,101 --> 00:22:33,144
Fine.

300
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:36,439
Then just die, okay? Stop tormenting me.

301
00:22:36,522 --> 00:22:37,982
Is that what you want?

302
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:40,610
Do you understand what it means to die?

303
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:43,321
[line disconnects]

304
00:22:44,781 --> 00:22:46,240
[phone buzzes]

305
00:22:46,324 --> 00:22:48,076
[drilling]

306
00:22:50,578 --> 00:22:51,746
[breathes shakily]

307
00:22:53,164 --> 00:22:54,165
<i>Don't forget…</i>

308
00:22:56,626 --> 00:22:57,627
<i>I'm…</i>

309
00:23:00,004 --> 00:23:01,130
[Su-ho laughs]

310
00:23:03,341 --> 00:23:04,634
<i>You killed me.</i>

311
00:23:06,135 --> 00:23:08,304
[laughing]

312
00:23:10,348 --> 00:23:11,682
[laughing continues]

313
00:23:13,434 --> 00:23:14,435
[video stops]

314
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:43,297
{\an8}THE LATE LEE SU-HO
MAY 7, 1991 - JUNE 14, 2018

315
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:02,150
FAITHFUL TO DUTY, FAITHFUL TO THE PEOPLE

316
00:24:02,233 --> 00:24:05,194
The captain thinks Paek Jun-beom
and Han Seol-ah were working together.

317
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:08,197
In Kim Yun-Ji's case and this accident.

318
00:24:08,698 --> 00:24:10,575
I still find that woman suspicious.

319
00:24:11,701 --> 00:24:14,245
Won't we find out who's behind this
if we find that car?

320
00:24:14,912 --> 00:24:18,749
Yeah, let's find that ghost car first then
we'll deal with the rest.

321
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:20,418
It's been a while since we teamed up.

322
00:24:20,501 --> 00:24:22,503
You cover the East side.
I'll take the West.

323
00:24:23,087 --> 00:24:24,088
Deal.

324
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:29,093
[determined music plays]

325
00:25:27,735 --> 00:25:28,903
[gasps]

326
00:25:30,696 --> 00:25:32,615
SANJUN JUNKYARD

327
00:25:50,174 --> 00:25:51,175
JUNKYARD

328
00:25:51,259 --> 00:25:52,385
[Gong] Geez, he's fast.

329
00:25:54,262 --> 00:25:56,264
I think it's that car over there.

330
00:25:59,308 --> 00:26:00,309
Hey.

331
00:26:01,185 --> 00:26:02,186
Hey.

332
00:26:29,338 --> 00:26:30,965
[Gong] There's nothing but trash in here.

333
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:35,761
1-HOUR FREE PASS

334
00:26:35,845 --> 00:26:38,264
- "Alpha Tower"?
- I know where this is.

335
00:26:40,182 --> 00:26:41,600
Call KCSI for fingerprints.

336
00:26:41,684 --> 00:26:44,103
I'll go see what Paek Jun-beom is up to.

337
00:26:51,319 --> 00:26:53,988
{\an8}[GPS] <i>You've reached your destination.</i>
<i>Ending navigation.</i>

338
00:26:54,071 --> 00:26:55,906
{\an8}ALPHA TOWER

339
00:27:00,453 --> 00:27:02,455
[dramatic music plays]

340
00:27:03,456 --> 00:27:04,707
[Jae-min] <i>He's unreal, you know?</i>

341
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:09,420
<i>Handsome, tall, smart.</i>
<i>Built a killer app and ends up super rich.</i>

342
00:27:09,503 --> 00:27:13,883
[Woo-seok] <i>Mr. Paek, may I ask you</i>
<i>what brings you here at this hour?</i>

343
00:27:19,597 --> 00:27:23,225
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

344
00:28:01,013 --> 00:28:02,348
I'm Paek Jun-beom.

345
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,811
Nice to meet you. I'm Paek Jun-beom.

346
00:28:07,478 --> 00:28:08,646
I guess you're left-handed.

347
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:12,066
Oh, it's just a habit of mine.

348
00:28:19,949 --> 00:28:21,575
[doorbell rings]

349
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:31,752
[stammers]

350
00:28:33,629 --> 00:28:35,005
Will these do?

351
00:28:37,091 --> 00:28:39,552
[chuckles] I've never done this before.

352
00:28:40,553 --> 00:28:41,637
What's this?

353
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:46,851
I mean… I thought our operation
was still ongoing, right?

354
00:28:49,395 --> 00:28:50,813
Oh.

355
00:28:57,194 --> 00:28:58,237
You're right.

356
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,739
I should react like this then.

357
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:13,252
[stammers]

358
00:29:14,003 --> 00:29:16,088
Anyway, happy birthday.

359
00:29:16,797 --> 00:29:17,965
It is your birthday, after all.

360
00:29:19,216 --> 00:29:20,217
Thank you.

361
00:29:22,511 --> 00:29:23,512
Come on in.

362
00:29:34,315 --> 00:29:36,066
It was sent anonymously.

363
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:39,904
These are the flowers
Su-ho always used to send.

364
00:29:41,739 --> 00:29:43,949
They even know details like that.

365
00:29:44,992 --> 00:29:48,621
I have no idea either
how they found out something like that,

366
00:29:49,914 --> 00:29:52,500
or what they could possibly want from me.

367
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:55,419
Any other messages?

368
00:30:04,178 --> 00:30:05,304
[groans]

369
00:30:07,556 --> 00:30:08,849
[grunts]

370
00:30:11,894 --> 00:30:12,895
[sighs]

371
00:30:14,104 --> 00:30:15,856
Whoever wrote this is left-handed.

372
00:30:16,899 --> 00:30:19,360
Mr. Paek is left-handed too.

373
00:30:28,953 --> 00:30:31,455
I mean, she always
spent her birthday with us.

374
00:30:31,539 --> 00:30:33,499
This is the first time she doesn't.

375
00:30:33,582 --> 00:30:35,918
[clicks tongue] It kinda stings.

376
00:30:38,003 --> 00:30:40,130
You went all the way to Daejeon
to buy this?

377
00:30:40,214 --> 00:30:42,466
That is some serious dedication.

378
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:44,760
Geez, I'm a picky eater,
so I don't eat much else,

379
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:46,220
but I like strawberry tarts.

380
00:30:46,929 --> 00:30:48,931
And you've never got me one
on my birthday.

381
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:51,642
You can have it all.

382
00:30:52,393 --> 00:30:54,186
Hmm, can I?

383
00:30:58,649 --> 00:31:00,401
[chuckles, gasps]

384
00:31:00,484 --> 00:31:01,735
Look at this color.

385
00:31:05,239 --> 00:31:06,240
[exclaims]

386
00:31:08,242 --> 00:31:09,493
- Is it good?
- It's so good.

387
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:12,913
Cheers.

388
00:31:17,418 --> 00:31:18,627
[sighs]

389
00:31:19,295 --> 00:31:21,714
We found the car thanks to your dashcam.

390
00:31:21,797 --> 00:31:22,923
It was a ghost car,

391
00:31:23,924 --> 00:31:26,176
and we tracked it entering
and leaving your complex.

392
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:30,681
Then the flowers
were definitely Mr. Paek's doing.

393
00:31:40,524 --> 00:31:41,692
We can't leave him be.

394
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:51,452
INSURANCE POLICY

395
00:31:56,290 --> 00:32:01,337
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-SEOK
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

396
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:06,425
If we move first and set a trap,
he'll fall for it.

397
00:32:07,426 --> 00:32:08,469
[scoffs]

398
00:32:09,053 --> 00:32:11,722
{\an8}MAIN COVERAGE:
NATURAL DEATH, GENERAL INJURY

399
00:32:17,144 --> 00:32:18,187
So, I'm a pushover?

400
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:20,939
Why does everyone do whatever they want?

401
00:32:22,524 --> 00:32:23,859
Seol-ah, listen.

402
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,569
Think about this calmly.

403
00:32:25,653 --> 00:32:27,488
If we do this,
the real culprit will show up.

404
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:31,241
Do you have any idea
how cruel this is to me?

405
00:32:32,034 --> 00:32:33,035
Seol-ah.

406
00:32:33,118 --> 00:32:35,954
What if I ended up just using you
and ditching you?

407
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:39,792
What if you really end up dead?

408
00:32:45,756 --> 00:32:46,757
I don't care.

409
00:32:48,717 --> 00:32:50,052
You hear me? I don't care.

410
00:32:56,266 --> 00:32:57,267
[sighs]

411
00:32:58,268 --> 00:32:59,520
You can use me instead.

412
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:07,319
Have you ever lived with guilt
because someone's death was your fault?

413
00:33:08,696 --> 00:33:10,531
Do you know how painful that is?

414
00:33:15,536 --> 00:33:16,537
I know how that feels.

415
00:33:18,622 --> 00:33:20,249
I lost my only family.

416
00:33:29,049 --> 00:33:30,384
After my parents divorced…

417
00:33:32,261 --> 00:33:33,887
I was raised by my grandmother.

418
00:33:36,807 --> 00:33:38,350
After she passed away,

419
00:33:39,977 --> 00:33:41,270
it was just the two of us.

420
00:33:50,362 --> 00:33:51,405
[scoffs, chuckles]

421
00:33:52,781 --> 00:33:56,368
Brother, when you told me
you were becoming a cop,

422
00:33:56,452 --> 00:33:58,996
the first thing I bought
was a first aid kit.

423
00:34:01,623 --> 00:34:03,459
Please don't get hurt again.

424
00:34:04,209 --> 00:34:07,880
I was supposed to be Woo-hee's big brother
and her mother and dad as well.

425
00:34:09,214 --> 00:34:10,716
But she took care of me instead.

426
00:34:11,592 --> 00:34:14,011
She was always strong. Stronger than me.

427
00:34:17,222 --> 00:34:18,390
After becoming a cop,

428
00:34:20,142 --> 00:34:22,394
I ran around day and night
chasing criminals.

429
00:34:24,688 --> 00:34:26,482
But I couldn't protect my own family.

430
00:34:31,987 --> 00:34:33,363
[Woo-seok sighs]

431
00:34:36,867 --> 00:34:40,078
If I had checked on her one more time,
I wouldn't have lost her.

432
00:34:45,292 --> 00:34:46,585
[Woo-seok breathes shakily]

433
00:34:47,336 --> 00:34:50,130
After I lost my sister, I threw myself
into cases like a madman.

434
00:34:50,839 --> 00:34:51,924
I worked myself to death,

435
00:34:52,007 --> 00:34:55,135
thinking it would help even a little
if I caught someone,

436
00:34:55,219 --> 00:34:58,931
but it… [scoffs] …but it never did.

437
00:35:00,432 --> 00:35:01,600
I realized this guilt…

438
00:35:03,477 --> 00:35:06,063
isn't something that goes away
just by saving someone else.

439
00:35:07,773 --> 00:35:09,149
It's not your fault Woo-seok.

440
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:11,443
You're wrong.

441
00:35:12,778 --> 00:35:14,071
It was my fault.

442
00:35:17,282 --> 00:35:18,826
I couldn't protect my sister.

443
00:35:23,539 --> 00:35:24,581
[chuckles]

444
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:27,960
We're both trapped in the same prison,

445
00:35:29,503 --> 00:35:34,758
living each day with the person
we couldn't protect in our hearts.

446
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:51,942
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

447
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:03,203
[intense music plays]

448
00:36:20,178 --> 00:36:21,179
You caught me.

449
00:36:21,263 --> 00:36:22,848
I was trying not to show it.

450
00:36:23,557 --> 00:36:26,101
You can't run auctions
without having a sharp eye.

451
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:28,520
[chuckles]

452
00:36:29,730 --> 00:36:31,231
Did you get hurt in the accident?

453
00:36:33,901 --> 00:36:34,902
Yeah.

454
00:36:40,866 --> 00:36:41,950
Then don't…

455
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:46,580
get hurt again.

456
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:51,919
[romantic music plays]

457
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:27,579
[phone buzzing]

458
00:37:29,790 --> 00:37:31,500
- [buzzing continues]
- [groans]

459
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:32,793
AHN YOUNG-SOO

460
00:37:35,837 --> 00:37:37,047
I'm sorry.

461
00:37:43,303 --> 00:37:44,846
- Hey.
- [Mr. Ahn] <i>Mr. Cha.</i>

462
00:37:44,930 --> 00:37:47,933
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin just woke up.
He'll be moved to a regular ward.

463
00:37:48,850 --> 00:37:49,935
Ahn, where are you?

464
00:37:50,936 --> 00:37:52,479
I'm outside the ICU right now.

465
00:37:53,689 --> 00:37:54,982
Listen carefully now.

466
00:37:55,857 --> 00:37:57,567
[thrilling music plays]

467
00:38:00,153 --> 00:38:02,447
Mr. Lee's awake. He's conscious again.

468
00:38:03,824 --> 00:38:06,159
No, just stay here.
It's better if you don't come with me.

469
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:08,161
Who knows what might happen?

470
00:38:08,245 --> 00:38:11,999
And the police keep suspecting you.
I don't want them to accuse you anymore.

471
00:38:13,709 --> 00:38:15,669
That sounds good. Give me a call.

472
00:39:18,565 --> 00:39:20,692
[line ringing]

473
00:39:29,993 --> 00:39:34,956
ROOM 2102
LEE *****-JIN

474
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:44,382
[intense music plays]

475
00:41:21,229 --> 00:41:24,024
[both grunting]

476
00:41:25,567 --> 00:41:26,776
[straining]

477
00:41:36,203 --> 00:41:38,205
[car alarm blaring]

478
00:41:38,288 --> 00:41:40,290
[groaning]

479
00:41:45,086 --> 00:41:46,087
[sighs]

480
00:41:46,755 --> 00:41:47,964
[groans]

481
00:42:10,862 --> 00:42:12,072
[Woo-seok] Are you awake?

482
00:42:12,906 --> 00:42:14,866
Hey! You should've followed him!

483
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:17,244
What? This was terrifying enough.

484
00:42:18,578 --> 00:42:21,581
- Hey. Did you do what I said?
- Yes.

485
00:42:25,377 --> 00:42:26,962
Geez, he really scared me.

486
00:42:29,756 --> 00:42:31,132
Hey, hey, hey.

487
00:42:32,175 --> 00:42:33,343
[exclaims]

488
00:42:37,013 --> 00:42:38,139
<i>Hey, hey! Why that…</i>

489
00:42:38,223 --> 00:42:39,224
[exclaims]

490
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:43,311
[sighs] This bastard is 4549.

491
00:42:43,395 --> 00:42:45,689
Wow. I totally knew
I'd pull this off to him.

492
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:50,193
He didn't have a doctor's coat on.

493
00:43:03,832 --> 00:43:04,833
Wow.

494
00:43:24,686 --> 00:43:26,021
"Pentobarbital."

495
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:28,398
What is it used for?

496
00:43:28,982 --> 00:43:30,817
An anesthetic used to put animals down.

497
00:43:31,526 --> 00:43:32,819
Huh?

498
00:43:32,902 --> 00:43:34,696
Honestly,
if it weren't for your foresight,

499
00:43:34,779 --> 00:43:37,157
Mr. Lee would've been in real danger then.

500
00:43:38,033 --> 00:43:39,075
Where is he now?

501
00:43:39,576 --> 00:43:40,952
Upstairs.

502
00:43:41,036 --> 00:43:42,037
The top floor.

503
00:43:44,998 --> 00:43:47,459
VIP1
AHN *****-SOO

504
00:43:53,506 --> 00:43:54,966
Do you recognize him?

505
00:43:55,550 --> 00:43:57,010
Yes, it's Jun-beom.

506
00:43:57,093 --> 00:43:59,012
[dramatic music plays]

507
00:44:19,449 --> 00:44:20,825
Was this taken in Syria?

508
00:44:22,911 --> 00:44:24,788
They were practically like brothers…

509
00:44:25,705 --> 00:44:27,123
until that accident.

510
00:44:28,875 --> 00:44:32,796
That day, an air strike wiped out
the entire refugee camp.

511
00:44:33,671 --> 00:44:35,340
Su-ho was killed on the spot.

512
00:44:35,924 --> 00:44:38,593
Jun-beom barely made it out alive.

513
00:44:40,261 --> 00:44:42,180
After being brought to Korea for surgery,

514
00:44:42,263 --> 00:44:43,556
he vanished.

515
00:44:44,391 --> 00:44:46,851
What's Paek Jun-beom
trying to hide, really?

516
00:44:47,894 --> 00:44:49,813
Are you sure it was Jun-beom who did it?

517
00:44:50,980 --> 00:44:51,981
But why?

518
00:44:54,317 --> 00:44:56,820
Mr. Lee, you know something important,
don't you?

519
00:44:57,445 --> 00:44:59,906
After Su-ho got dumped by his girlfriend,

520
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:01,783
he said he wanted to die.

521
00:45:01,866 --> 00:45:03,701
He didn't even bother taking cover.

522
00:45:04,828 --> 00:45:07,247
Honestly,
I think it was basically suicide.

523
00:45:10,792 --> 00:45:13,920
Jun-beom got hurt
while trying to save him.

524
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:16,441
[phone buzzes]

525
00:46:28,620 --> 00:46:29,621
CHA WOO-SEOK

526
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:31,915
[Woo-seok] <i>I found</i>
<i>where Lee Su-ho's ashes are.</i>

527
00:46:33,541 --> 00:46:35,502
<i>If it's too much, I'll come with you.</i>

528
00:47:06,866 --> 00:47:09,202
{\an8}THE LATE LEE SU-HO
MAY 7, 1991 - JUNE 14, 2018

529
00:47:19,963 --> 00:47:21,631
[Kwang-jin] <i>He was an orphan</i>
<i>with no family,</i>

530
00:47:22,423 --> 00:47:24,717
<i>so I placed his ashes in a columbarium.</i>

531
00:47:40,066 --> 00:47:44,571
Seems like Mr. Paek
wanted me to come all the way here.

532
00:47:49,117 --> 00:47:53,913
The truth is, I knew that Su-ho
decided to end his own life.

533
00:47:54,914 --> 00:47:56,332
It was his choice.

534
00:48:07,885 --> 00:48:08,970
<i>Don't forget…</i>

535
00:48:11,431 --> 00:48:12,473
<i>I'm…</i>

536
00:48:13,182 --> 00:48:14,726
[laughing]

537
00:48:16,144 --> 00:48:17,437
<i>You killed me.</i>

538
00:48:21,691 --> 00:48:22,692
[sighs]

539
00:48:23,359 --> 00:48:25,278
I couldn't bring myself to tell you.

540
00:48:25,361 --> 00:48:26,863
I was afraid you'd think

541
00:48:27,697 --> 00:48:29,616
I was behind Su-ho's death too.

542
00:48:30,825 --> 00:48:32,035
What do you mean?

543
00:48:33,119 --> 00:48:35,413
I overheard what you said
to Detective Gong.

544
00:48:38,541 --> 00:48:40,918
She's the type who could control
anyone she wanted to.

545
00:48:41,002 --> 00:48:43,421
And there might be another person
involved too.

546
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:45,923
[sighs]

547
00:48:47,592 --> 00:48:49,427
I guess you didn't hear
what I said after that.

548
00:48:49,510 --> 00:48:52,263
I just meant that that's how the cops
might see it.

549
00:48:53,848 --> 00:48:54,849
You're wrong.

550
00:48:56,184 --> 00:48:58,186
I don't suspect you anymore, Seol-ah.

551
00:48:58,269 --> 00:48:59,270
I trust you.

552
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:03,232
That's why I'm telling you
everything here.

553
00:49:06,361 --> 00:49:09,113
He kept saying he was going to die,
like it was a habit,

554
00:49:09,197 --> 00:49:10,490
so I told him to die

555
00:49:12,408 --> 00:49:14,202
- and stop tormenting me.
- [sighs]

556
00:49:15,411 --> 00:49:16,663
If only I hadn't said that

557
00:49:18,414 --> 00:49:20,291
the last time we spoke…

558
00:49:20,375 --> 00:49:21,709
Don't beat yourself up.

559
00:49:24,045 --> 00:49:25,838
It's not your fault.

560
00:49:28,174 --> 00:49:30,093
I think I know why he sent this now.

561
00:49:31,594 --> 00:49:36,599
Mr. Paek is just getting revenge on me
in Su-ho's place instead.

562
00:49:38,309 --> 00:49:40,144
He's using every means he can

563
00:49:40,978 --> 00:49:42,814
in order to make me miserable.

564
00:49:48,236 --> 00:49:49,404
They sent us a gift.

565
00:49:51,072 --> 00:49:52,573
Why don't we return the favor?

566
00:49:58,579 --> 00:50:00,415
DNA MATCH,
VEHICLE 4549, EVIDENCE IN ATTEMPTED MURDER

567
00:50:00,498 --> 00:50:04,377
The same DNA was found in the
ghost vehicle and on the doctor's coat,

568
00:50:04,460 --> 00:50:05,795
and it matched Kim Sung-hae,

569
00:50:05,878 --> 00:50:07,380
age 34 who served time for manslaughter.

570
00:50:07,463 --> 00:50:08,464
KIM SUNG-HAE

571
00:50:08,548 --> 00:50:11,217
He's a former non-commissioned officer
with special training

572
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:13,553
and deployment experience in Syria.

573
00:50:13,636 --> 00:50:16,180
You're saying he was in Syria
with Paek Jun-beom?

574
00:50:16,264 --> 00:50:18,891
So, Paek's the torso
and Kim Sung-hae's just the tail.

575
00:50:18,975 --> 00:50:20,685
We can't link him

576
00:50:20,768 --> 00:50:23,521
just based on him going in
and out of the company building

577
00:50:23,604 --> 00:50:25,523
unless we conduct a search and seizure.

578
00:50:25,606 --> 00:50:26,607
Well, let's get him.

579
00:50:27,233 --> 00:50:29,944
Catch Kim Sung-hae first
for attempted murder.

580
00:50:31,154 --> 00:50:32,155
All right. [sighs]

581
00:51:03,561 --> 00:51:05,730
Nice to see you, Ms. Han.
I'll take you to Mr. Paek's.

582
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:28,336
Mr. Paek will be here shortly.

583
00:51:28,419 --> 00:51:30,463
Please have a seat
and make yourself comfortable.

584
00:51:30,546 --> 00:51:32,089
Sure, no problem.

585
00:51:37,845 --> 00:51:39,096
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

586
00:51:51,484 --> 00:51:52,485
DELETING…
SELECTED FILES: 30

587
00:51:52,568 --> 00:51:54,320
INTEGRATED CONTROL CENTER
CCTV SYSTEM

588
00:51:54,403 --> 00:51:58,032
As instructed, we're deleting all the
footage that shows your movements, sir.

589
00:51:58,115 --> 00:52:00,785
Delete the recent footage
from the parking lot entrance too.

590
00:52:01,369 --> 00:52:03,079
[facility manager]
Will that be everything, sir?

591
00:52:04,372 --> 00:52:05,581
No problem.

592
00:52:06,999 --> 00:52:10,378
DELETING…
SELECTED FILES: 382

593
00:52:16,133 --> 00:52:17,468
VEHICLE ACCESS LOG PROGRAM
WAITING FOR CONNECTION

594
00:52:17,552 --> 00:52:19,804
The black sedan would've been caught
on the parking gate cameras

595
00:52:19,887 --> 00:52:21,347
going in and out of the building.

596
00:52:22,473 --> 00:52:23,516
THANK YOU
GOODBYE

597
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:30,690
Boss, take a look at this.

598
00:52:30,773 --> 00:52:34,235
It's an automatic license plate
recognition system.

599
00:52:34,318 --> 00:52:37,029
It captures the plates
and the person in the car too.

600
00:52:37,613 --> 00:52:42,159
But nobody treats it like a big deal,
so the security is a total mess.

601
00:52:42,243 --> 00:52:44,287
It's basically, "Come on in."

602
00:52:44,370 --> 00:52:45,830
Look, see. It works on everything.

603
00:52:45,913 --> 00:52:47,707
Then bring me everything.

604
00:52:47,790 --> 00:52:49,083
Yes, sir.

605
00:52:50,877 --> 00:52:52,295
Right to it.

606
00:52:56,507 --> 00:52:57,508
Huh?

607
00:52:57,592 --> 00:52:58,593
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

608
00:52:58,676 --> 00:52:59,844
Hold on.

609
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:02,722
These bastards are deleting
everything in real time.

610
00:53:03,806 --> 00:53:06,934
Damn it. They must have realized
the ghost car got flagged.

611
00:53:07,018 --> 00:53:09,854
That's probably why Paek Jun-beom
isn't showing up right now.

612
00:53:24,577 --> 00:53:26,037
[phone buzzes]

613
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:35,129
HAN SEOL-AH

614
00:53:39,634 --> 00:53:41,928
Uh, I'm sorry. Something came up.

615
00:53:42,011 --> 00:53:43,387
Have you been waiting long?

616
00:53:43,471 --> 00:53:45,306
Not at all. I just got here too.

617
00:53:45,806 --> 00:53:46,807
Have a seat.

618
00:53:48,100 --> 00:53:50,144
[sighs]

619
00:53:51,729 --> 00:53:52,939
First.

620
00:54:03,658 --> 00:54:06,744
YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED TO ROYAL AUCTION
KOREA'S PREMIER FINE ART AUCTION HOUSE

621
00:54:06,827 --> 00:54:07,828
An invitation?

622
00:54:08,788 --> 00:54:12,583
Yes. It's for a preview event
we're holding for our VIP guests,

623
00:54:12,667 --> 00:54:16,545
and it's also be the first public showing
of the Stiller piece.

624
00:54:17,129 --> 00:54:18,547
Yes, I should be there.

625
00:54:18,631 --> 00:54:20,549
That's my beloved child after all.

626
00:54:22,009 --> 00:54:25,012
Everyone's been wondering
who the Stiller's owner is.

627
00:54:26,180 --> 00:54:29,684
Are you sure you're okay with your
identity being revealed like this?

628
00:54:31,018 --> 00:54:32,228
[thrilling music plays]

629
00:54:35,481 --> 00:54:37,942
[inhales sharply]
I wanted to stay mysterious

630
00:54:38,025 --> 00:54:39,986
but you kind of shattered that for me.

631
00:54:42,238 --> 00:54:46,367
Oh, and about <i>An Orphan from Syria</i>…

632
00:54:51,580 --> 00:54:54,583
It seems like a pretty meaningful piece
to you.

633
00:54:57,128 --> 00:55:00,506
May I ask why you decided to consign it?

634
00:55:06,053 --> 00:55:07,722
Hmm…

635
00:55:10,558 --> 00:55:13,102
I wanted to show more of myself.

636
00:55:15,021 --> 00:55:16,981
It feels like me without the mask.

637
00:55:17,898 --> 00:55:19,150
[inhales sharply]

638
00:55:19,233 --> 00:55:21,777
Truth is, I used to have nothing,

639
00:55:21,861 --> 00:55:24,280
like an orphan in the middle of a war.

640
00:55:24,905 --> 00:55:26,365
[inhales sharply] Honestly,

641
00:55:27,283 --> 00:55:31,412
it's still strange
to see myself sitting here.

642
00:55:35,458 --> 00:55:41,005
It takes a very thick mask to stand there
and pretend that everything is fine.

643
00:55:47,762 --> 00:55:48,929
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

644
00:55:51,265 --> 00:55:53,059
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

645
00:55:57,980 --> 00:55:59,231
[gasps]

646
00:56:00,524 --> 00:56:05,946
Found it. Wow, that was so close.
I barely got my hands on it.

647
00:56:06,030 --> 00:56:08,699
If I had taken a bit longer,
this data would've been gone.

648
00:56:08,783 --> 00:56:10,159
It was Paek Jun-beom.

649
00:56:10,242 --> 00:56:12,286
{\an8}[Jae-min] Man,
this is why he wiped everything.

650
00:56:12,369 --> 00:56:15,039
Geez, this bastard is really meticulous.

651
00:56:15,122 --> 00:56:16,665
One scary piece of work, huh?

652
00:56:16,749 --> 00:56:19,085
What an evil bastard. Shit.

653
00:56:22,088 --> 00:56:23,297
That mask…

654
00:56:24,924 --> 00:56:27,176
how about you take it off now?

655
00:56:32,932 --> 00:56:34,475
Who are you really?

656
00:56:35,309 --> 00:56:37,061
Why did you approach me

657
00:56:37,144 --> 00:56:39,188
when you already knew Su-ho?

658
00:57:04,421 --> 00:57:07,508
Do you think I'm trying to blame you
for Su-ho's death?

659
00:57:09,218 --> 00:57:10,553
Is that what you think?

660
00:57:11,595 --> 00:57:14,140
[ominous music plays]

661
00:57:17,810 --> 00:57:19,019
Or do you think…

662
00:57:29,321 --> 00:57:31,365
I'm getting revenge on you?

663
00:57:41,333 --> 00:57:42,835
No, that's dangerous.

664
00:57:43,544 --> 00:57:44,545
Boss, wait up!

665
00:58:04,023 --> 00:58:07,234
{\an8}SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM DONGJUN
FOR HIS APPEARANCE

666
00:58:30,633 --> 00:58:31,842
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>I don't get it.</i>

667
00:58:31,926 --> 00:58:34,428
{\an8}<i>Even if this is a revenge</i>
<i>on Su-ho's behalf,</i>

668
00:58:34,511 --> 00:58:36,680
{\an8}this is way too extreme.

669
00:58:36,764 --> 00:58:38,766
{\an8}It's similar to my sister's accident.

670
00:58:38,849 --> 00:58:42,436
{\an8}<i>Criminals stick to familiar tactics</i>
<i>and repeat what's worked before.</i>

671
00:58:42,519 --> 00:58:45,940
{\an8}I'm also chasing the person
who ruined my life.

672
00:58:46,023 --> 00:58:47,691
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>Then let's uncover them.</i>

673
00:58:48,234 --> 00:58:50,819
{\an8}<i>Let's uncover the hidden truth together.</i>

674
00:58:50,903 --> 00:58:54,448
{\an8}So, isn't there something
you want to tell me?

675
00:58:54,531 --> 00:58:57,993
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>We can finally find out</i>
<i>what Paek Jun-beom was trying to hide.</i>

676
00:58:58,077 --> 00:58:59,411
{\an8}Let go!

677
00:58:59,495 --> 00:59:01,080
{\an8}[Jun-beom] <i>I finally got it out there.</i>

